flowRoot.flowPara: Caption: Avida is a digital evolution platform consisting of (a) organisms that taken in inputs from the environment and perform logical tasks on these to generate an output using (b) their genome as well as the memory available to them in the form of registers and stacks. If the output is satisfactory, the organisms are awarded CPU cycles that essentially increase the rate at which the genome is traversed. (c) Every time the genome is executed completely, the organisms reproduce giving rise to an offspring in the nearby grid-cell. (d) For both signalling and reproduction, only the moore neighborhood of its cell is accesible to the organism. (e) Demes are artifically restricted uniclonal sub-populations that replicate as a whole and consist of 25 single organisms. (f) Each deme starts with a single organism that then divides and propogates to fill the entire deme. Organisms in the deme, while being uniclonal, can use spatial information and signalling to differentiate into multiple phenotypes. These organisms acquire resources individually but donate it to the deme using a specific genomic instructions. (g) The deme replicates as soon as the deme resource amount crosses the replication threshold (1000 units in this case). Deme replication is mutation prone and this generation of variation through mutation allows the evolution of novel genotypes over evolutionary time.
